### Light can behave like waves or like particles

Light (or, in general, electromagnetic radiation) can undergo _superposition_ and _interference_. These are _strong evidences that electromagnetic radiation behaves like waves_.

However, in order to explain the photoelectric effect, electromagnetic radiation needs to be treated as if they were particles.

